Galax

Wisconsin: Sauk County

W-facing slope under an oak tree.
*Galax urceolata* (Poiret) Brummitt (G. 'aphylla').
Formerly a dairy farm, the plants on a steep slope
with cliffs that had been fenced off to keep the cows
out. Deep within a natural area.
Two plants 1 ft. apart, one 12 in. in diam. with 21
stems this year, one 4 in. in diam. "We've been
watching these plants since 2001, and we always
thought it was *Sullivantia*, because some botanist told
us it was."

10N 05E 04 SW4SE4       980 ft.

Locality of Denzer- Rick and Deborah Bott's property,
S7635 Pine Hollow Dr., 3.2–3.3 mi. (airline distance)
NE of Leland, 1.8 mi. (airline) NNW of Denzer.

Bott, Rick       s.n.
Bott, Deborah       8/Jul/2009
